  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>ChinaFAQs experts from the Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory have <a href="http://eaei.lbl.gov/publications/china-energy-and-emissions-paths-2030">projected that China‚Äôs coal use will peak in 2020</a> due to increasing energy efficiency and slowing energy demand.  As ChinaFAQs expert Ailun Yang discussed, the <a href="../blog-posts/what-future-king-coal-china">continued expansion of coal in China faces many problems</a>, such as economic problems with the power sector, strict control of energy prices, and the rising public concern over health and environmental impacts.  In addition to these already substantial challenges, rising coal use in China will also run into substantial obstacles in the form of water stress.</p></div>
