                <span class="field-content"><a href="../library/testimony-mikkal-herberg-us-china-economic-and-security-review-commission-january-26-2012">Testimony by Mikkal Herberg Before the U.S.-China Economic and Security Review Commission, January 26, 2012</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"><img src="../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/Herberg_Testimony2.png" alt="" title="" width="142" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-library-file-fid">
                <div class="field-content"><div class="filefield-file"><img class="filefield-icon field-icon-application-pdf"  alt="application/pdf icon" src="../sites/all/modules/filefield/icons/application-pdf.png" /><a href="../files/chinainfo/Herberg_USCC&#32;testimony_26&#32;2012.pdf" type="application/pdf; length=75401">Herberg_USCC testimony_26 2012.pdf</a></div></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>I first would like to thank the members of the Commission for the opportunity to testify to this important group. It is an honor and a privilege.</p>

<p>I have been asked to speak about China‚Äôs approach to securing its energy supplies and implications for the United States. I will discuss China‚Äôs approach, whether it is impacting global energy markets and the competitive prospects of American energy companies, how Beijing‚Äôs energy security drive is influencing maritime territorial and sea lane disputes in the seas around Asia, and some suggestions on U.S. policy towards the developments.</p></div>
