  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../blog-posts/what-look-chinas-12th-five-year-plan">What to Look for in China‚Äôs 12th Five-Year Plan?</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-library-file-fid">
                <div class="field-content"></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>China‚Äôs annual political meetings begin on Thursday March 3 and the major outcome will be the announcement of the 12th Five-Year Plan (2011-2015). Votes at both the advisory China People‚Äôs Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC, opening March 3) and the National People‚Äôs Congress (NPC, opening March 5) are not in question. But the content of the Five-Year Plan, as well as various government work reports and major pieces of legislation, are only revealed during the meetings.</p></div>
